      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Before the summer is well set in\nthere will be two new divisions estab-\nllshed on the Northern Pacific, if pres\nent plans do not miscarry. One of\nthese will be from Pasco to Auburn,\nand be named the Cascade division, and\nwill take off 1876 miles from the Idaho\ndivision and los miles from the Pacific\ndivision.\n\n\nThe new steamer Hope has been COM\npleted and it is planned to run pas\nsenger line on Lake Pend d'Oreille in\nconnection with the railroads, taking\nin the towns of Hope, Blacktail Sand\npoint and all intermediate points."
    }
